 Tejano perspective. This book complements and continues the history begun in Tejano Origins in Eighteenth-Century San Antonio, which Gerald E. Poyo edited with Gilberto M. Hinojosa.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aMexican AmericanszTexasxHistoryy18th century. 0aMexican AmericanszTexasxHistoryy19th century. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh1 aCastillo Crimm, Ana Carolina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHardin, Stephen L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLack, Paul D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMatovina, Timothy M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPoyo, Gerald E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPoyo, Gerald E., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aTeja, Jesus F. de la, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTijerina, Andrés, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/76570240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292761728423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292761728/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK